Staff Reporter Mamelodi Sundowns midfielder Andile Jali appeared briefly at the Hatfield Community Court on Tuesday after he was allegedly charged for ‘assault and malicious damage to property’. The midfielder has since been released on bail. The events that led to the arrest of the 28-year-old is still unclear, as he was taken to Boschkop police station after the alleged incident, believed to have taken place at his home. Jali spent Monday night in jail following his arrest for domestic violence. The case has since been postponed until 05 December for further investigation.